text.tspan: With over 40 miles of carriage roads,
you’ll be biking for hours around the
park. If you get bored of that you can
get on actual bike paths and even
other roads like gravel roads and
paved roads.
For all you hike lovers you’ll get
you’re kicks here. There is over 150
miles of endless trails to experience.
Explore the mountain
tops, have an adventure in the forest,
and look upon the sights along the
rocky coastlines.
Looking for a nice relaxing fishing
trip well Acadia has you
covered. Acadia is the home to 29
different species of freshwater fish
among the many bodies of water.
There’s a numerous number
of lakes, ponds, and streams, but if
that’s not your thing you can
just fish in the ocean the park is on
an island after all.
Need a break from life and
othertroubles well why not camp
out. Acadia does not allow
“out-of-bounds” camping or camping
out in cars, but they have
four wonderful campgrounds to
choose from.
Kayaking is a fun relaxing time on the
water and is super easy for beginners
to do. With several kayak rentals all
over and to choose from you can
basically kayak anywhere in or around
the park. Also, Acadia offersseveral
coastal tours for those who don’t
really know where they want to go.
Acadia is nation park located on the Mount Desert Island in Maine. This national park has been beloved
by all for its wonderful lush green forests, great ponds and rivers, beautiful pinetree covered mountains, and two
very popular beaches. There’s tons to explore and do here and since the park is opened 24 hours 7 days a
week you’ll have all the time in the world.
You can find over 400 different types of wildlife all over the park grounds like red foxes, white-tailed
deer, and the adorable puffins. Come each season and see what newbeautiful creature is roaming the
park. For those not interested in animals come and see the over 1000 wonderful plant life
scattered all around park. You’ll love seeing the cool blue Wild Blue Iris, the wild Lily-of-The-Valley, the
calming Starflower, and from August to September see the Goldenrods in full bloom.
Adventure through the park and see the many historical landmarks
Acadia has to offer. Find memorials like the John D. Rockefeller Memorial
and the Robert Abbe memorial. Walk under the historical cobblestone
bridges. Witness the eye catching lighthouses and even see them
light up red during the night.
